x4freetext: Tagged-photon facility.
Lund University racetrack microtron.
The target  of  enriched  (> 98 %)  40Ca was a  solid
cylinder with  dimensions  42-mm  diameter  x 100-mm
length.
Each neutron detector consisted of 64 TOF
spectra which contained real coincidences  with  the
tagger focal plane and a random background.
NE213A Liquid scintillator.
Pulse   shape   analysis  for  separation  of
neutron events from the background of photons.
Statistical errors.
In total,  the upper limit for systematic
uncertainty is 17 %:
Uncertainty in the neutron yield arising from
the fitting of the  random  background  in  the  TOF
spectra (10 %).
Uncertainty  in  the   neutron   transmission
efficiency (9 %)  due  to  flight  path  and neutron
absorption cross section uncertainties.
Uncertainty in the  estimated efficiency  of
the neutron spectrometer (7 %).
Data from Figs.  3 - 5 were compiled  at  the
Russia MSU SINP CDFE by V.V.Varlamov.
Corrected by V.Varlamov: AUTHOR, doi.
